OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1784720909
OL,3,CHumanitarian worker monitored in
OL,4,CLondon hospital after potential Ebola
OL,5,Cexposure
OL,7,FA humanitarian worker is being
OL,8,Fmonitored at a specialist hospital in
OL,9,FLondon after potential exposure to the
OL,10,FEbola virus.
OL,12,FThe UK resident was medically
OL,13,Fevacuated from the Democratic Republic
OL,14,Fof the Congo where they had been
OL,15,Ftreating patients with the disease,
OL,16,Fthe UK Health and Security Agency
OL,17,F(UKHSA) said.
OL,19,FIt said they have been evacuated as a
OL,20,F"highly precautionary measure".
OL,26,@|D@AOU
