FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1784720909
OL,3,CHumanitarian worker monitored in
OL,4,CLondon hospital after potential Ebola
OL,5,Cexposure
OL,7,F"The incubation period of Ebola ranges
OL,8,Ffrom two to 21 days and the individual
OL,9,Fwill be closely monitored and required
OL,10,Fto isolate throughout this period."
OL,12,FEbola is a highly dangerous pathogen.
OL,14,FUnlike airborne diseases it spreads
OL,15,Fthrough direct contact with bodily
OL,16,Ffluids.
OL,18,FSymptoms come on suddenly and start
OL,19,Flike the flu with headaches, fever and
OL,20,Ftiredness.
OL,26,@rD@cO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/5
